ch as Catherine Macaulay and Mary Wollstonecraft. These individuals and groups which emerged in the eighteenth century established 'intellectual spaces' for the emergence of women public intellectuals in subsequent centuries. It also examines women public intellectuals in the US including Samantha Power, Anne-Marie Slaughter, Elizabeth Warren, Condoleezza Rice, Susan Rice, Hillary Clinton and Sheryl Sandberg.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831111966880 cprintz978144734135240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447341130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447341130/original  a978-3-11-119668-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles